   - `<meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">`: Sets the viewport to the width of the device's screen and initial scale to 1.0, which is necessary for responsive design.
   - `<title>Document</title>`: Sets the title of the webpage to "Document".

4. `<link rel="stylesheet" href="css/login.css">`: This line links an external CSS file named "login.css" to style the HTML elements within this document. This allows for separation of concerns, where the structure and content are defined in HTML, and the appearance is defined in CSS.

5. `<body>`: This section contains the visible content of the webpage.

