     - `<input placeholder="Name" name="name" type="text">`: This input field allows users to input their name. The "placeholder" attribute provides a hint to the user about what to enter, and the "name" attribute specifies the name of the input field when the form is submitted.
     - `<input placeholder="Password" name="password" type="password">`: This input field allows users to input their password. The "type" attribute is set to "password" to obscure the characters entered by the user.
     - `<input class="sub" type="submit">`: This input field represents a submit button that users can click to submit the form. The "class" attribute is set to "sub", which could be used to apply specific styling from the linked CSS file.

   - `<a href="/">Go back to login page</a>`: This is an anchor element (a link) that points to the "/" URL. When clicked, it will redirect users back to the login page.

6. `</body>`: Marks the end of the visible content of the webpage.

7. `</html>`: Marks the end of the HTML document.
